this remedy may be obtained by using an enforcement procedure under the Act and provides that if the court does not otherwise have jurisdiction of the parties, the law relating to the type of enforcement served shall be used to determine issues ancillary to the entry of a charging order such as jurisdiction, liens, and priority of liens. Amends the Probate Act of 1975. Modifies provision that states that all claims against an estate are barred 2 years after decedent's death, by adding an exception that states: if the estate is opened 21 months after the date of death or later, a claim must be filed not less than 6 months after the first notice is published or 3 months from the date of mailing or delivery of the required notice, whichever is later.", "pending_committee_id": 0, "committee": [], "referrals": [{"date": "2011-02-24", "committee_id": 235, "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 35, "name": "Rules"}, {"date": "2011-03-01", "committee_id": 219, "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 35, "name": "Judiciary I - Civil Law"}, {"date": "2011-04-07", "committee_id": 254, "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 36, "name": "Assignments"}, {"date": "2011-04-27", "committee_id": 277, "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 36, "name": "Judiciary"}], "history": [{"date": "2011-02-24", "action": "Filed with the Clerk by Rep. Sidney H. Mathias", "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 35, "importance": 1}, {"date": "2011-02-24", "action": "First Reading", "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 35, "importance": 0}, {"date": "2011-02-24", "action": "Referred to Rules Committee", "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 35, "importance": 1}, {"date": "2011-03-01", "action": "Assigned to Judiciary I - Civil Law Committee", "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 35, "importance": 1}, {"date": "2011-03-09", "action": "Do Pass / Short Debate Judiciary I - Civil Law Committee; 011-000-000", "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 35, "importance": 1}, {"date": "2011-03-09", "action": "Placed on Calendar 2nd Reading - Short Debate", "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 